<br>
Lacerate Artery.  <br>
Min Level: 65 <br>
Refresh: 1 hour <br>
<br>
Result: The rogue reaches around from behind his intended victim and rips his neck wide open with a clean slash.  Effect: Damage equal to the rogues attack rating + bleeding damage of 2x atk rating over 18 seconds. <br>
<br>
Limitations: <br>
<br>
The rogue must be behind the target, <br>
<br>
duelist doesn't increase the damage done, <br>
<br>
only humanoid mobs 1-60 and all players within pvp range are viable targets,<br>
<br>
no mob may be effected by this ability more than once every minute, <br>
<br>
and the rogue may not backstab for 20 seconds after the blow is delivered. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taarna1vz>Taarna1 VZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/20/02 11:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue Burn</span><hr size=1> You say MB is over powered in pvp, so you want it nerfed for wizzys and a rogue MB instead... jesus you are not very bright. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taarna1vz>Taarna1 VZ</A> at: 11/20/02 11:58:15 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aerimusshadowborn>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 229<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/20/02 3:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue Burn</span><hr size=1> &quot;I have come around to the idea that mannaburn should remain in pvp along with super HT. In a similar vein I believe a rogue aa should be added.&quot;<br>
<br>
If I had my way I'd simply remove it from pvp but since this doesn't seem to be happening I'd be almost as happy if a rogue super uber death to all ability were added. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jeebuzweezard>Jeebuz Weezard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/20/02 6:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> sigh</span><hr size=1> Sigh. So if you don't get your way (other insta-kills nerfed) you want your own? Holy crap dude, give it a rest. You're a rogue, if you suck at pvp, you suck at pvp. Start a new class. I think this rogue burn idea is terrible, heh. And it's never going to be implemented because YOU'RE the only one that thinks its a good idea.<br>
<br>
You already have the highest DPS of all the melee classes, over a long period of time you outdamage us, and yet you still cry NERF wizards or BUFF US UP? Give it a rest, its not going to happen. It's illogical. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aerimusshadowborn>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 230<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/20/02 8:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sigh</span><hr size=1> Having a high sustained dps in pve really doesn't mean quite as much in pvp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jeebuzweezard>Jeebuz Weezard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/23/02 7:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Well, by your logic then we should get more spells that allow us to do a shitload of damage using very little mana as to be more effective in the long term. Therefore having a high sustained DPS. You get one or the other dude, not both. Unless you're a mage. =( <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=syrne>Syrne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 224<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/23/02 8:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> In case you haven't noticed, EQ is more of a PvE game than a PvP game.  Face it, rogues aren't of the best design for PvP.  They rock PvE though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raystonn>Raystonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 175<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/23/03 6:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> The classes are not supposed to be balanced in each area of offense, defense, etc.  Each has his specialty.  Wizards are supposed to have the best offense and worst defense.  Warriors should have the best defense with the worst offense.  Other classes fit somewhere in the middle.<br>
<br>
If you make everyone do equivolent damage over time then you should also make them dodge, deflect, or otherwise absorb the same amount of damage over time with defensive skills/spells.  Once you've done that, all the classes become pretty much the same, but with different graphics and other minor differences.  It doesn't matter where the damage is coming from (sword, spell, etc.), as long as it's guaranteed to be a certain amount over a large period of time, now does it?  I would hate for all classes to be pretty much the same in these regards.  How boring...<br>
<br>
Each class should be specialized.  Give warriors the ability to tank very well.  In exchange for that superior defensive ability, their offensive ability should suffer.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>That</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is how you balance classes.<br>
<br>
What that means is we are going to have a rock-paper-scissors scenario in 1 on 1 fights.  Class A will have the advantage over class B in a duel.  In turn, class B will have the advantage over class C, and class C will dominate class A.  That's just the way it is going to have to be unless you want every class to be identical, just with differing graphics and cosmetic styles of play.<br>
<br>
-Raystonn<br>
